HEADWORD: oversimplified
<hw>oversimplified</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>simplified excessively so
as to distort or misrepresent; -- of facts, assertions, or
communications. Contrasted with <ant>overcomplicated</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> simplistic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

